==English==
===Etymology===
From the French [[poignard]], from [[poign]] ([[fist]]), from the Old French, from the Latin [[pugnus]].
===Pronunciation===
===Noun===
# A small [[knife]] or [[dagger]], popular during the [[Wikipedia:Middle Ages|Middle Ages]] and [[Wikipedia:Renaissance|Renaissance]].
===Verb===
'''Poniard''' ([[poniards]], [[poniarded]], [[poniarding]])
#To stab with a poniard.